1
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,640
All right, Mr. Wu.

2
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:37,400
Get down.

3
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:43,600
What you said is

4
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,520
so magnificent and righteous.

5
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,680
It's simply romantic heroism.

6
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:51,120
You want to carry it all by yourself, huh?

7
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:51,780
Sister Jia.

8
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,120
No matter who carries it.

9
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,080
Although we participated in the competition secretly,

10
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,200
we did it after finishing

11
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,759
all the data accounting.

12
00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:00,080
We didn't delay any of our regular work.

13
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,040
Is it worth trying so hard for a competition?

14
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:07,640
Yes,

15
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,600
we just want to try our best.

16
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,560
Right,

17
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,090
we just want to try our best.

18
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,250
I will try my best with them.

19
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:19,400
All right.

20
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,920
If you guys have the guts to compete secretly,

21
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,079
don't embarrass me.

22
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,360
You made a plan and ranked over 50th.

23
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:28,240
Those who know would think you competed secretly.

24
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:31,500
Those who don't would think I didn't teach you well.

25
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,360
We are already optimizing the plan

26
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,360
and will catch up.

27
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,600
How will you catch up? Let me see.

28
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,560
Where is the plan? How will you optimize it?

29
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,440
Bring it here.

30
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,890
Please come in, Jia.

31
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,520
Here.

32
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,400
Have some water, Jia.

33
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,880
If your plan can't use the satellite toolkit,

34
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,480
the data calculation volume is too large.

35
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,940
You need to optimize this.

36
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,440
Sorry, Jia.

37
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:52,840
It's done.

38
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,720
The plan is done.

39
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:58,720
Wake up.

40
00:03:58,880 --> 00:03:59,920
Wake up.

41
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,380
Jia has sorted out the plan for us.

42
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,200
Okay, I'll get going.

43
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,940
I'll walk you out, Jia.

44
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,320
No need. Get some rest.

45
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,050
I'll walk you. Look at the time.

46
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,200
We in aerospace engineering

47
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:15,330
should take better care of female colleagues. Let's go.

48
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,240
All right, stop walking me.

49
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:20,920
This is far enough.

50
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:23,760
No, I have to see you get in the car.

51
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:27,040
I'm in high spirits after a happy event.

52
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:29,170
I'm motivated to work on the proposal.

53
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:30,920
Jia.

54
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,880
I don't think you're a runaway princess.

55
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:36,120
You,

56
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,440
you're our lucky star.

57
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,280
The morning star, our savior,

58
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:43,960
All right, all right.

59
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:44,520
our big star.

60
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,120
Enough.

61
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,120
Star after star.

62
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:46,800
All right.

63
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,200
Save your flattery

64
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,860
and think about the proposal.

65
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,500
But let me tell you,

66
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,880
a competition is a competition, and work is work.

67
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,210
You need to do both well.

68
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,720
Don't worry, Sister Jia.

69
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,340
Sister Jia.

70
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,460
Anything else?

71
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,280
No matter what others think of us

72
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,360
or say about us,

73
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,480
we all appreciate you.

74
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,900
Especially me.

75
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,120
Save it.

76
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,680
Just put more effort into your work from now on.

77
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,440
I will.

78
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,200
You really don't have to walk me out.

79
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,760
I'm buying breakfast on the way.

80
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:24,680
Go back and get some rest.

81
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:25,920
I wish.

82
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,160
I'll wash up when I get back

83
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,890
and continue calculating data in the afternoon.

84
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:41,640
Thanks.

85
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,340
Half for each of us.

86
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:07,920
Mr. Li,

87
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,160
the usual.

88
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:09,680
Okay.

89
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,200
Why is there no news about your promotion yet?

90
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,520
Soon. In a few days.

91
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:19,060
Interact more with the leaders at crucial moments.

92
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,080
Give this to Mr. Qin later.

93
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,000
Say it's a specialty from our hometown.

94
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,800
Then the leader won't feel pressured to accept it.

95
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,120
Thank you.

96
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:33,000
This is unnecessary.

97
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,260
Why is it unnecessary?

98
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,920
By getting closer to the leader,

99
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,560
he will see your performance

100
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,600
and understand your difficulties.

101
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,440
Have I been teaching you in vain?

102
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,840
Why don't you understand?

103
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,680
You aerospace people,

104
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,480
no one's education is worse than anyone else's.

105
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,600
Working as a team,

106
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,860
you can't tell who made the achievement.

107
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,400
In the end, doesn't it depend on who has

108
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,120
a stronger presence in front of the leader?

109
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,240
I know, but...

110
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:00,000
But Old Qin doesn't like this kind of stuff.

111
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,040
You can't get angry at a smiling face.

112
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,640
It's human nature.

113
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:06,000
If we don't get the promotion this year

114
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,760
and have no quota,

115
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,080
we won't be assigned an apartment in Space City.

116
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,520
We live so far apart,

117
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,080
and you're busy with work.

118
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,240
I can't commute back and forth every day.

119
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,320
Over time,

120
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,880
how is this different from a long-distance relationship?

121
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,360
Why don't you get it?

122
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,840
I know Old Qin.

123
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:23,040
He won't accept these things.

124
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,840
Besides, the professional title

125
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,770
is evaluated by the entire system.

126
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,090
Mr. Qin doesn't have the final say.

127
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,240
Li Qitan.

128
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:33,800
Are you the one who doesn't understand, or am I?

129
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,720
You have never

130
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,380
considered our future at all.

131
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,240
Of course I have.

132
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,040
We've been dating for so long,

133
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,440
and it's always been me accommodating you.

134
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,920
No matter how important my plans are on weekends,

135
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,480
I cancel them to see you.

136
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,920
You live in a dorm.

137
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,640
If we miss each other,

138
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,400
we won't see each other on weekends.

139
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,360
We live in the same city,

140
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,040
but we live apart.

141
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,560
When you have an important task

142
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,600
and the space city is closed off,

143
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,200
we don't see each other for a month or two.

144
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,080
Are you going to make me live like this forever?

145
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:01,480
We're going to have problems sooner or later.

146
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:01,880
Qu.

147
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,080
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

148
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,680
Qu.

149
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,240
I...

150
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,000
Mr. Li.

151
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,680
This must be your wife, right?

152
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,680
Well, I'll get going.

153
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:22,760
Who is she?

154
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:23,920
An intern.

155
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:38,760
Mr. Qin.

156
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,480
Qitan.

157
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:41,020
Are you looking for me?

158
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:41,640
What's up?

159
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,080
Nothing much.

160
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,780
You don't look like nothing's wrong.

161
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:47,770
What is this?

162
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,840
This is tea sent from my hometown.

163
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,120
I don't usually drink tea.

164
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:51,880
For me?

165
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:53,080
Yes, for you.

166
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,740
It's from Xiao Feng, isn't it?

167
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:56,720
Right.

168
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,920
About the promotion.

169
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,320
About the promotion.

170
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,080
This Xiao Feng is really good to you.

171
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,360
You should be more attentive to her in the future.

172
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,080
Yes.

173
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:06,880
Thank Xiao Feng for me.

174
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,440
Okay.

175
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,620
As for this tea,

176
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,200
I'll accept it.

177
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,080
Do you know what to say when you get back?

178
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,080
I know, Mr. Qin.

179
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:13,840
Thank Xiao Feng.

180
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:14,360
Okay.

181
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,900
Take care, Mr. Qin.

182
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:18,240
Yanyan.

183
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,000
Mr. Qin.

184
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,080
Is the pantry out of tea?

185
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,000
Yes, we just ran out.

186
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,920
That's perfect.

187
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,720
Qitan contributed some good tea.

188
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,850
Let everyone try it.

189
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:25,680
Sure.

190
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,120
Don't forget to tell everyone

191
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,180
that it's Qitan treating them to tea.

192
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,080
Okay.

193
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,040
Thanks for the tea, Mr. Li.

194
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:32,880
Thank you.

195
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,200
Thank you, Mr. Li.

196
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,010
You're welcome.

197
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,200
Good tea.

198
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,000
Still working?

199
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,560
Director Cao.

200
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,400
Lao Qin.

201
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,410
Have you booked a place for your birthday?

202
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:53,680
What?

203
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:56,280
Just find an excuse for everyone to relax.

204
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:59,360
You are giving me another task.

205
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,960
What else can I say?

206
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,690
I will follow the arrangement.

207
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,000
China Aerospace.

208
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,040
Is there anything else?

209
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,560
Nothing.

210
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:20,720
I just wanted

211
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,880
to see how you've been doing lately.

212
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,090
Lately, I...

213
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,960
Come, have a seat.

214
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,220
Things are as usual for me lately.

215
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,240
What do you mean 'as usual'?

216
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,900
I'm asking about your personal life.

217
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,760
My personal life?

218
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,960
My personal life

219
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:43,620
is pretty good.

220
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,520
Work has been very intense.

221
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:50,160
Xingqiao is about to launch soon.

222
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,440
My heart is still

223
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,420
pounding a bit.

224
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,980
But please rest assured, sir.

225
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,890
It will be completed smoothly.

226
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,560
Alright, alright, alright.

227
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:00,560
Don't interrupt.

228
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,740
You know exactly what I'm asking.

229
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,520
What?

230
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,160
Personal situation.

231
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:07,560
I mean your personal relationship status.

232
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,440
How old are you?

233
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,720
What's there to be embarrassed about?

234
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,240
Then just say it straight.

235
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,680
Come on, give me a report.

236
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:14,760
Recently,

237
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:15,160
any problems?

238
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,680
I'm not part of your Women's Federation.

239
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:18,000
Why are you still asking this?

240
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,320
What does this have to do with the Women's Federation?

241
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:23,920
I'm in charge of all sorts of things at the Flight Control Center.

242
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,680
As an old colleague,

243
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:28,600
I just want to show some concern for your personal life.

244
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,530
Is that not okay?

245
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:30,680
Okay.

246
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,200
Besides,

247
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,800
I'm also representing the organization

248
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,860
to show some concern for older single colleagues like you.

249
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,640
I have an old classmate.

250
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,080
She's quite a catch.

251
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,440
She's pretty

252
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,800
and gentle.

253
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,580
What do you say?

254
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,680
If you're interested,

255
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:03,560
I can arrange a meeting.

256
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,880
Plan it out and set it up.

257
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,360
Oh, no.

258
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:11,680
What's wrong?

259
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,600
I... I have an appointment.

260
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,040
I...

261
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,960
How could I forget?

262
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,320
Seriously.

263
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,640
Think about it.

264
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,170
I wasn't even going to celebrate my birthday.

265
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,320
What's the point of celebrating?

266
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,720
But Director Cao wouldn't hear of it.

267
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,680
She said we might as well apply for a team building event

268
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,120
and celebrate together.

269
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,090
Just to liven things up.

270
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,560
Coming all this way

271
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,160
just to get a piece of my cake.

272
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,760
Pathetic.

273
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:54,220
So this is the Muxing Team you recruited?

274
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,320
What about them?

275
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,320
I saw one of them in the computer lab.

276
00:12:58,920 --> 00:12:59,760
What computer lab?

277
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:00,920
The computer lab.

278
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,800
They want to use computers.

279
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,840
There's only a week left. They're crazy.

280
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,960
For a competition.

281
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,290
Did you ask them to join?

282
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,320
They wanted to compete themselves.

283
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,880
Nan, I've sent you the data.

284
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,720
Jia's optimized plan

285
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,360
did save a lot of time,

286
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,240
but we still need to study the core algorithm

287
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,100
and speed it up.

288
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,280
I heard

289
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:34,960
